## CBUXO FLAGS (all parts)

- **Non-analytical reader risk: HIGH.** Congressional data feels abstract and distant. Every tab must open with a personal, visceral entry point — not a chart.
- **Emotional arc (all parts):** Recognition ("I knew they were out of touch") → Structural reframe ("I didn't know it was this documented") → Accountability ("This is not an accident") → Agency ("Here is what I can check")
- **Simplified graphics rule (locked May 25, 2026):** Pared down, dumb simple. One chart per tab maximum. Big numbers with one sentence of context. Side-by-side comparisons over multi-variable charts. The reader should understand every visual in under 3 seconds.
- **No individual member profiles.** State-level aggregates only. This is about the system, not gotcha journalism.

